NAME
    cp - copy files and directories

SYNOPSIS
    cp [-r] <source> <dest>

DESCRIPTION
    Copies files or directories from source to destination.
    If dest is a directory, copies into it with the same name.

OPTIONS
    -r, -R, --recursive
            Copy directories recursively

EXAMPLES
    cp /tmp/file.txt /tmp/backup.txt
        Copy a file

    cp /tmp/file.txt /home/root/
        Copy file into directory

    cp -r /home/root/project /tmp/backup
        Copy directory recursively

SEE ALSO
    mv, rm, cat
